------------------------------------------------------------------------
1)		WHAT'S THAT?
------------------------------------------------------------------------
The DigiXound Project aims to be a complete audio framework for 
professional performers and developers.
uStream is the streaming kernel of DigiXound, thinked to be lightweight,
cross platform and derived from Danubio streaming architecture
(http://www.danubio.org).



------------------------------------------------------------------------
2)		REQUIREMENTS
------------------------------------------------------------------------
- CMake >= 2.2.0;
- other... ;-(



------------------------------------------------------------------------
3)		INSTALL
------------------------------------------------------------------------
To install you need to have CMake (http://www.cmake.org)
version 2.2.0 or above installed in your system. 
Then CD IN THE SOURCE DIRECTORY and depending of your OS:

==> Unix command build:
./configure
make
make install (as root or with proper rights)

==> Unix interactive build:
./bootstrap
ccmake .
make
make install (as root or with proper rights)

==> Win32 or Apple:
>>not yet tested!<<
You need also a "make"-like program (on Win32, nmake could be good).
Try the CMake Gui program to select source directory and flags.
The run CMake process. At the end you will be able to compile with
the selected environment (MinGW, Visual Studio etc...).

Finally there are some options you can change through configure script
or CMake gui:

PREFIX : the install prefix (configure with -DPREFIX=/new_prefix) 



